# Assignment Management System

The assignment system handles the complete lifecycle from creation to grading, with support for multiple question types and AI-powered features.

## Core Data Models

### Assignment Structure
**File**: [src/types/assignment.ts](mdc:src/types/assignment.ts)

```typescript
export interface Assignment {
  id: string
  lesson_id?: string           // Optional lesson association
  title: string
  description?: string
  instructions?: string
  questions: Question[]        // Array of questions
  total_points: number        // Sum of all question points
  due_date?: string
  published: boolean          // Draft vs published state
  created_at: string
  updated_at: string
  lesson?: {                  // Populated lesson data
    title: string
    slug: string
  }
}
```

### Question Types
The system supports four main question types:

#### Multiple Choice
```typescript
export interface MultipleChoiceQuestion extends BaseQuestion {
  type: 'multiple-choice'
  options: string[]           // Answer choices
  correctAnswer: number       // Index of correct answer
  explanation?: string        // Why answer is correct
}
```

#### Open Response (AI Graded)
```typescript
export interface OpenResponseQuestion extends BaseQuestion {
  type: 'open-response'
  rubric: RubricCriterion[]          // Grading criteria
  correctConcepts?: string[]         // Key physics concepts
  commonMisconceptions?: string[]    // Wrong ideas to check for
  sampleAnswer?: string             // Example good answer
  autoGrade?: boolean              // Enable AI grading
  gradePrompt?: string             // Custom grading instructions
}
```

#### Numerical Answer
```typescript
export interface NumericalQuestion extends BaseQuestion {
  type: 'numerical'
  correctValue: number        // Expected numeric answer
  tolerance?: number          // Acceptable error range
  unit?: string              // Required unit
  unitOptions?: string[]     // Unit choices for students
}
```

#### Essay (Manual Grading)
```typescript
export interface EssayQuestion extends BaseQuestion {
  type: 'essay'
  rubric?: string           // Grading guidelines
  minLength?: number        // Minimum character count
  maxLength?: number        // Maximum character count
}
```

